HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 225
BY REPRESENTATIVE ECHOLS
ENVIRONMENT: Urges and requests the Department of Environmental Quality, the
Governor's Office of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness, the Ouachita
Parish Police Jury, and the municipalities within Ouachita Parish to study parish-
wide solid waste, debris removal, and disaster resiliency services
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana Department of Environmental Quality, the Governor's
3 Office of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness, the Ouachita Parish
4 Police Jury, and the municipalities within Ouachita Parish to jointly study a
5 parish-wide solid waste, debris removal, and disaster resiliency service model; to
6 evaluate consolidation of services; to explore public-private partnerships and funding
7 mechanisms; and to report findings and recommendations to the Legislature of
8 Louisiana.
9 WHEREAS, Ouachita Parish includes multiple municipalities and unincorporated
10 areas currently utilizing separate solid waste collection, debris removal, and cleanup
11 systems, resulting in fragmented services, inefficiencies, and inconsistent disaster response
12 capacity; and
13 WHEREAS, Louisiana routinely experiences hurricanes, floods, ice storms,
14 tornadoes, and other natural disasters that generate massive volumes of storm debris
15 requiring rapid and coordinated removal and disposal which often must also comply with
16 procedures of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA); and
17 WHEREAS, parish-wide coordination of trash service, vegetative debris collection,
18 construction and demolition waste management, and emergency cleanup operations can
19 improve efficiency, reduce taxpayer costs, enhance resiliency, and expedite disaster
20 recovery; and
