1 (5) Public-private partnership opportunities.
2 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study of resiliency and infrastructure
3 improvements shall include consideration of the following:
4 (1) Hardened landfill and transfer station planning.
5 (2) Recycling and waste diversion systems.
6 (3) Storm surge and flood-resistant facilities.
7 (4) Long-term mitigation strategies eligible for federal funding.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study of governance and funding models
9 shall include consideration of the following:
10 (1) Parish-wide waste authorities or service districts.
11 (2) Intergovernmental agreements.
12 (3) User-fee structures.
13 (4) FEMA, Environmental Protection Agency, and infrastructure grant programs.
14 (5) Private operator concessions or hybrid models.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the agencies and local governments referenced
16 herein shall submit a joint written report to the House Committee on Municipal, Parochial
17 and Cultural Affairs and the House Committee on Transportation, Highways and Public
18 Works no later than December 1, 2026, that includes the following:
19 (1) Feasibility findings.
20 (2) Cost comparisons.
21 (3) Recommended governance structure.
22 (4) Proposed implementation timeline.
23 (5) Legislative actions needed.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
25 secretary of the Department of Environmental Quality, the director of the Governor's Office
26 of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness, the president of the Ouachita Parish
27 Police Jury, and the mayors and governing authorities of Monroe, Richwood, Sterlington,
28 and West Monroe.
